{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"0782f66a529ccd24e18226f5eebab20a90bea166"},"timestamp":1254341332,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyODQ4NDUx","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/254","origin":"github"},"title":"test subclasses of core PMCS","message":"One of the common failure modes for partcl is that a subclass of a parrot core PMC causes a problem due to code in the PMC that assumes (accidentally) that it will never be subclassed.\n\nSo, one way to protect HLL authors is to, for each core PMC test, have a corresponding test file that runs similar/identical tests except with a subclass. (The subclass can be a basic subclass with no overrides.)\n\nIt would be nice if the testing framework did this automatically, so that test writers did not have to keep 2 files per PMC in sync whenever tests were added.\n\nOriginally http://trac.parrot.org/parrot/ticket/1082","files":null}]}